net.sf.mmm.transaction.api

Interface TransactionExecutor

  • All Superinterfaces:
    EventSource<TransactionEvent,TransactionEventListener>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractTransactionExecutor, JpaTransactionExecutor, JtaTransactionExecutor, NoTransactionExecutor, SpringTransactionExecutor

    @ComponentSpecification
public interface TransactionExecutor
extends EventSource<TransactionEvent,TransactionEventListener>
    This is the interface for a component capable of executing your code within a transaction. It is a front-end to an underlying transaction-manager that makes your transactional code easy and less error-prone.
    Additionally it allows you to add custom hooks to your transaction-management if you perform all transaction operations via this API.
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)

    • Method Detail

      • doInTransaction

        <RESULT> RESULT doInTransaction(Callable<RESULT> callable)
                         throws Exception
        This method executes the given callable in the context of a transaction.
        Therefore this method opens a new transaction, invokes the callable in a surrounding try-statement so that the transaction is automatically committed if your callable succeeds while a rollback is performed in case it fails (throws anything).
        Type Parameters:
        RESULT - is the generic type returned from your callable.
        Parameters:
        callable - is the Callable to be executed within a transaction.
        Returns:
        the result of the callable.
        Throws:
        Exception - if the callable failed.
